TY  - JOUR
AB  - In the session of Congress that closed August 11, 1939, Congress passed four important acts dealing with tax matters: (1) the Internal Revenue code; (2) the Public Salary Tax act, 1939; (3) the Revenue act of 1939; and (4) Social Security act amendments of 1939.
