TY  - JOUR
AB  - Payment of punitive rates for overtime hours has become widespread lately through union agreements, the N.R.A., and the Fair Labor Standards act. This practice raises interesting theoretical issues, and casts some doubt on the validity of the marginal productivity theory of wages. Where overtime rates are paid for normal work there is evidence of labor "exploitation." Payment of overtime rates for emergency work represents a price discrimination that favors labor.
